I'M IN LOVE ..and it's becoming unhealthy. lol. Many months ago my eyes fell upon a beautiful talented man, it was love at first sight... and my recent encounter with him this last saturday has left me shaken!! Last night I had a dream about him.. he found me at a show, we laughed, he asked me to dance, then he kissed me!!! ohhhh it was amazing... until brett walked in and I had to choose who I wanted to be with. HAHAHA. It was the saddest and happiest dream I've ever had lol. Why do I love this god given gift wrapped in cute paper and topped with good hair... because the music that comes from this beautiful mouth makes me melt.. because the boy can dance... (even in my dream) because he's just plain cute (2nd in from the right).. because he titled this picture: friends are friends forever if the lord is lord of them because he has gorgeous brown eyes and the cutest little butt.. and because when i talked to him on saturday.. (well when brett and andrew decided they wanted to profess my love to him for me!) he just looked at me.. smiled..and said: "hey.. we can work something out". Then every time we walked past his merch table after that I would look over and he would just smile, oh that smile.. In conclusion.. you all think i'm crazy now (heck even i think i'm crazy)..but man oh man i've got it bad and i just had to gush : ) peace and love. p.s. sorry about this brett haha.. but remember I LOVE YOU MORE!!.... i think.. mmmk so this weekend has been (i don't even know a word that describes it).... Friday: school then work. Then a call from my magnificent boyfriend...(be jealous, your boyfriend will NEVER be this awesome)... telling me to leave work NOW and come to soma!! He was standing outside with a sign that said "i need tickets. I'll give you candy" and had gotten tickets to the falloutboy, starting line, panic! at the disco, has been sold out forever show! 3 in fact. So andrew came too :] Every single band was amazing... and then came FOB.. i have never seen such a good performance. The whole place was going crazy. I'm not a big pete fan but he was hotter than anyone at soma that night... omg once again there's no words to describe. Anyway i danced and sang my heart out.. then went home and went to bed. Saturday: Woke up and went to breakfast with my family, aubs fam, and brett. Then we all went to the pumpkin patch... and there my friends i fell in love, with a baby cow. It was the cutest thing ever. it kissed my whole face. Anyway we got our pumpkins, brett played football with "the men" hahahaha, and then we all carved them. At about 2:45 brett and i left and made our way up to L.A.... why you ask.. to go to the myspace concert duh! lol. Kind of lame at first.. everything you would imagine when a tone of myspace whores get together. But it got a lot better when the all american rejects started.. then came Jim Adkins i thought it was very good but everyone booed him because he was "too slow".. LAME-OES. Last but definately not least i was devirginated of a dashboard show. Chris Carrabba is the best thing to walk this earth. the end. Today: brett and i missed church this morning : / oops. I have to finish my halloween costume :))) Then i'm going to mama mia with my sister, mom, aub, denise, cousin, aunt t, aunt c... LADIES NIGHT!! haha so there's my weekend...

brett's pumpkin :) my pumpkin :) (she's listening to headphones)

wow.
have you ever had one of those days where you feel like you're the only person alive.....

have you ever had one of those outsider days where you just kind of stand back and watch the world?  
it really puts things in perspective...   OBSERVATIONS:

  • today at school i walked past a row of computers and every single screen had myspace on it. (I can't say too much because i'm on livejournal right now being a bigcupolamesauce)
  • on my way to class i repeatedly counted from 5-0 to see how long it took for me to find someone on their cell phone.. i never got past 4. i wonder what would happen if we took everyones cell phones away... i bet the mental institutions would be full of people going crazy. Then someone would invent some new medication that would numb you and "make it all better".
  • while i was walking through the grass the sprinklers turned on... and i kept on walking. Who cares if we're wet. who said it's not ok if we have moisture on our clothes and god forbid our hair get a little crazy. OH NO.
  • today in my feminism class i was taught that "women are like birds in a cage made by men". and that we shouldn't change our last name to our husbands because we are an individual, they don't own us. oh and send your children to day care because you are a women and it's not your job to take care of them. geeze! I say be a mother, be a wife, have a job, be loving, be considerate, be emotional, be compassionate, be amazing, BE A WOMEN, be happy!! it's really not that hard.... dang feminazis!
  • something as simple as croutons and ranch is just so good. i swear the basics, that's where it's at.
  • people amaze me. they can be so inspiring, or just dreadful. or sometimes they just seem not to exist. who decides which one they are? our own perception of it all? or are they really that way? and why? and why is someone that seems so sweet so grouchy sometimes? are they just mean and bitter and they try their best to act sweet and civil? or do they just have something bad going on? if they do.. what is it? what's so bad that they'll waste a day of their life being miserable. JUST SMILE. why does everyone walk around frowning look at the ceiling if you have to it really makes everything so much better. (someone once told me that and i swear it works :] )
    (sorry if i lost you on that one)
  • can someone please help me? why is partying cool? why does everyone do it? what's the attraction to it? man-ho's, sluts, barf, std's, rape, pregnancy, death, strangers, hang-overs.. oh wow you got me, dudebro i'm totally partying tonight.
  • i've never seen the oc or laguna beach..... haha why is that such a phenomen.

ok this is getting boring.. and it could take hours. so i'm done now. my apologies if that was stupid, boring, lame, obvious, or whatever.. but you could have stopped reading at any time : ) you all have a wonderful day... and smile remember things can always get worse. live for the moment and LOVE. like crazy too... love anyone and everyone, unconditionally. like he does..
"you should love one another. Just as I have loved you" -john 13:34

p.s. i'm taking my lip ring out. it's the most annoying thing in the world. i'm pretty much over the whole decorate your face thing. it's a face, not a christmas tree. you live and learn. advice: don't pierce your face. it's bad news. and it hurts bad. really bad. love your face loverfaces.

peace

Warm October nights

watching eyes shut tight

keep me warm and we can make it

So I could watch you dream some more

Spring break was glorious. the first week was a lot of fun and the second was simply wonderful.... saturday night i came home to a polka dotted house!! It was quite a sight. As soon as we saw it, brett and i got out and started looking at everything THEY WERE EVERYWHERE. While admiring the work guess who shows up to take pictures.. that's right the suspects returned to the scene of the crime and we were there to catch them. After a couple of rounds of driving around the block honking, moaning, and yelling WPP they finally stopped to confess! Total: -433 on the house -61 on my car P.S. I'm the luckiest girl ever ♥

great weekend so far. I was supposed to be camping but that got cancelled.

 

friday night after unpacking everything i was able to go to... DAPHNE LOVES DERBY with brett!!!! I had so much fun. daphne was amazing as usual, and brett was awesome as usual. sooo it was a pretty good night. thursday: say anything. one word: excited.... then i came home and made a midnight run to in-n-out with allie. mmmmmmmmm

 

this morning i woke up at the butt crack of dawn to go to a wonderful pat and oscars meeting. yay. then i came home and decided to go to downtown for a little photography session. got some good ones. it was an experience: hit on by bums, losing our car, learning how to use a parking meter, and one way streets...can i just say ???what. Anyway went to get my pics developed. when i came out i go to, what i thought was my car. haha too bad it wasn't. I opened the door with my key and start to get in when i see a carseat. hmmm last time i checked i didnt have any kids but who knows. anyway i realize this is not my car and start walking away (yes i left the door open, sorry i panicked!). Later when i went to pick up el fotos i came out and the lady was there. she was confused and just staring at her door (because it was open). she started looking all around, and i just walked past. hahaha i felt so bad, i broke into her car!!! what can i say i'm a thug.

 

went to the play tonight with the girls, good times. they did a great job. andddddd now i'm home updating this thing woohoo. but i'm off to bed to get some rest for my exciting day. tomorrow i will no longer be a 6 flags virgin yesssssssss.

peace out

 

p.s. starlight starbright first star i see tonight wish i may wish i might, i wish... someone would go to the beach with me i'm having withdrawals.! please : )

I'm missing your laugh. How did it break?

 

And when did your eyes begin to look fake?

Since I met you,
I've been entranced with who you are.
Such a different life,
Your home a world afar.

I have read of your homeland,
Of its beauty and serenity.
I can see its beaches and jungles,
Its fields of plenty.

I can see its perfection,
I can see it through you.
Through every thought and emotion,
Through everything you do.

You are so special,
So very very unique.
For you I would swim the widest ocean,
And climb the tallest peak.

There is so much of you I don't know,
So much that it frustrates me.
Yet of what I have learned of you,
Utterly fascinates me.

I will patiently wait for you,
I will wait for a sign.
I hope that somehow... someday,
You will be mine.
